React = CamelCase 
Javascript = hyphen-lowercase

could just toss it in a style.scss file 
h1 style={{ color: 'red' }}>Book Store</h1>
outer { } inject JS into the JSX file 
inner { } create a JS object 

for ease, store style attributes in a variable 
OK TO CALL IT IN TOP LEVEL 

values can be in string, or if number, px is assumed
EX: 

const styles = {
  color: 'darkcyan',
  background: 'mintcream',
  marginTop: '100px'
  marginBottom: 25
};

export class StyledClass extends React.Component {
  render() {
    return (
      <h1 style={styles}>
        Book Store
      </h1>
    );
  }
}